#### font-size ####

Size of the font, specifies one of the following values:

named-font-size
:     Set of keywords that indicate predefined font sizes. Scale according to the user's font setting preferences. 
      Possible values include the following: *xx-small*, *x-small*, *small*, *medium*, *large*, *x-large*, *xx-large*;

relative-size
:     Set of keywords that are interpreted as relative to the font size of the parent object. 
      Possible values include the following: *larger*, *smaller*;

length
:     [Length Units] value;

percentage
:	    Integer, followed by a percent (%). The value is a percentage of the parent object's font size;
      

Example:

```css
/* <length> values */
font-size: 12px;
font-size: 0.8em;

/* <percentage> values */
font-size: 80%;
```

</section>

## Length Units ##

Floating-point number, followed by an absolute units designator (cm, mm, in, pt, pc, or px) or a relative units designator (em or ex). For more information about the supported length units, see the CSS Length Units Reference.